Sequence Information.Peptide Name: CFPS_AMP_3 (cell-free protein synthesis-AMP 3, AI predicted AMPs, Lys-rich; UCLL1)
Sequence Information.Source: AI predicted, machine learning prediction of known protein sequences

Literature.Author: Pandi A, Adam D, Zare A, Trinh VT, Schaefer SL, Burt M, Klabunde B, Bobkova E, Kushwaha M, Foroughijabbari Y, Braun P, Spahn C, Preußer C, Pogge von Strandmann E, Bode HB, von Buttlar H, Bertrams W, Jung AL, Abendroth F, Schmeck B, Hummer G, Vázquez O, Erb TJ. 2023
Literature.Title: Cell-free biosynthesis combined with deep learning accelerates de novo-development of antimicrobial peptides.

Sequence Information.Comments: Sequence analysis: APD analysis reveals that this sequence is most similar (37.04%) toNA-CATH. K: 31%; F=R: 14%; G: 12%.Activity: active against E. coli (MIC 12.5 uM), B. subtilis (MIC 0.8 uM), A. baumannii clinical strain (MIC 6.3 uM), Enterobacter spp. (MIC >25 uM), K-pneumoniae DSM 30104 (MIC>25 uM), P. aeruginosa DSM 1117 (MIC 9.4 uM), S. aureus DSM 11729 MRSA (MIC 12.5 uM), E. faecium (MIC 1.6 uM), Y. pestis EV76 (MIC 12.5 uM), B. anthracis Sterne (MIC 12.5 uM), and S-pneumoniae D39 (MIC > 25 uM).Toxicity: Human RBC: HC50>250 uM, not hemo.lytic.Resistance development:no:bacteria:E. coli: E. coli did not develop resistance to the peptide after 21 passages. In contrast, the MIC of imipenem increased by 8 fold.
